  "text": "# Retry with Exponential Backoff Pattern Analysis\n\n## Kubernetes (kubernetes/kubernetes)\n\nKubernetes implements exponential backoff through multiple layers:\n\n### Core Implementation\n1. **wait/backoff.go** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/backoff.go`): Contains the main `ExponentialBackoff` function and `Backoff` struct. The `ExponentialBackoff` function (line 475) repeats a condition check with exponential backoff using `backoff.Step()` to determine sleep duration. The `ExponentialBackoffWithContext` variant (line 493) adds context cancellation support.\n\n2. **exponentialbackoff package** (`pkg/util/goroutinemap/exponentialbackoff/exponential_backoff.go`): Provides the `ExponentialBackoff` struct that tracks error state and manages retry duration. It starts with 500ms, doubles on each error, and caps at 2 minutes + 2 seconds.\n\n### Usage in Controllers\nMultiple Kubernetes components use the exponential backoff pattern:\n- Volume attachment/detachment: `pkg/controller/volume/attachdetach/reconciler/reconciler.go`\n- Persistent volume management: `pkg/controller/volume/persistentvolume/pv_controller.go`\n- DRA plugin management: `pkg/kubelet/cm/dra/plugin/dra_plugin_manager.go`\n- Node shutdown: `pkg/kubelet/nodeshutdown/nodeshutdown_manager_linux.go`\n- Plugin management: `pkg/kubelet/pluginmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go`\n- Volume manager: `pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/reconciler/reconciler_common.go`\n- Watchdog: `pkg/kubelet/watchdog/watchdog_linux.go`\n- CSI plugin operations: `pkg/volume/csi/csi_attacher.go`, `csi_plugin.go`, and `nodeinfomanager.go`\n- Nested pending operations: `pkg/volume/util/nestedpendingoperations/nestedpendingoperations.go`\n\n## Grafana (grafana/grafana)\n\nGrafana's Git repository implementation uses the `retry.ExponentialBackoffRetrier` from the nanogit module in `apps/provisioning/pkg/repository/git/repository.go`. The `defaultGitRetrier()` function (line 898) configures:\n- **Total attempts**: 8 (1 initial + 7 retries)\n- **Initial delay**: 100ms\n- **Backoff multiplier**: 2.0 (exponential)\n- **Maximum delay**: 5 seconds\n- **Jitter**: Enabled\n- **Total retry window**: ~10 seconds\n\nRetries occur on network errors, HTTP 5xx errors (for idempotent operations), and HTTP 429 (rate limiting).\n\n## Prometheus (prometheus/prometheus)\n\nPrometheus implements exponential backoff in remote write operations:\n\n### Queue Manager Implementation\nThe `storage/remote/queue_manager.go` file contains multiple backoff implementations:\n\n1. **sendWriteRequestWithBackoff** (around line 814): Implements retry logic with configurable min/max backoff. It doubles backoff on each attempt until reaching the maximum duration.\n\n2. **sendMetadataWithBackoff** (line 590): Sends metadata batches with backoff using `sendWriteRequestWithBackoff`.\n\n3. **AppendSamples/AppendExemplars** (lines 720-774): Implements exponential backoff for enqueueing samples and exemplars. Starts with 5ms, doubles on each failed enqueue attempt, and caps at `t.cfg.MaxBackoff`.\n\n### Client-side Error Handling\n`storage/remote/client.go` defines `RecoverableError` type that wraps errors with retry-after information, enabling proper backoff handling for transient failures.\n\nPrometheus uses an exponential backoff strategy where the delay starts small (5ms for enqueue operations) and doubles with each failed attempt, capped at a configured maximum. The `Retry-After` header from responses can override the default backoff duration."
